article.headline: Morehead St. 84, N. Carolina A&amp,T 61
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. -- Terrance Hill and Demonte Harper scored 19 points each to lead Morehead State to an 84-61 rout of North Carolina A&T on Sunday. Four players scored in double figures for the Eagles (2-0) as Kenneth Faried had 14 points and Ty Proffitt 10. Leading 10-6, Morehead State blew it open early on a 15-3 run in the Global Sports Invitational matchup. Faried's jumper capped the run for a 25-9 lead with 8:18 left in the first half. The two teams had similar shooting performances with the Eagles making 40.6 percent (28 of 69) and the Aggies (0-2) hitting 40.1 percent (19 of 47), but North Carolina A&T committed 23 turnovers. Morehead State brought the lead to as many as 29, 80-51, on Arthur McMillan's layup with 4:38 to play. Marc Hill led four Aggies in double figures with 13 points. Adrian Powell scored 11 and R.J. Buck and Thomas Coleman chipped in 10 each.
